verses.text:
Thy will was in the builder's thought;
Thy hand hath all our longings wrought;
Through mortal motive, scheme and plan,
Thy wise, eternal purpose ran.

No lack Thy perfect fullness knew;
For us the daily bread renew;
In house of prayer and praise this home
Of rest. Here may Thy children come.

O Father! deign these walls to bless;
Make this the abode of righteousness;
Here let Thy gate and fortress be
Thy lead us from ourselves to Thee!
